    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a high-upside slate today, anchored by the elite 87.42 score for **Yordan Alvarez**. He is our clear top play against Michael Lorenzen; his 0.393 xwOBA, combined with a significant +14% park factor boost and the protection of batting second, makes him a locked-in core piece. Joining him as high-ceiling starters are **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (71.81) and **Trea Turner** (69.86). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a strong +14% dynamic platoon advantage against Joe Boyle, while **Trea Turner** remains a primary focal point despite the moderate SP skill of Tyler Mahle, as his leadoff status and speed metrics continue to anchor our 5x5 rotation. **Colt Keith** (69.64) is similarly positioned to provide explosive production from the top of the order against Bailey Ober.\n\nStrategy dictates we keep a close eye on our bench, where **Carson Benge** (46.03) was the hardest exclusion from the starting lineup. While his platoon edge is favorable, his projected efficiency fell just short of the thresholds set by our mid-order hitters, particularly as we prioritize **Victor Scott II** (62.18) for his elite speed profile in the nine-hole. Caution is advised for **Kazuma Okamoto**, who faces the stiffest test of the day against Shohei Ohtani; his low score of 42.45 is suppressed by a brutal -19% SP skill penalty, leaving him squarely in the \"marginal\" start category. Furthermore, most of our starters remain \"Lineup Pending,\" introducing variance in expected batting order positions; we must remain vigilant regarding **Dillon Dingler** and **Logan O'Hoppe**, as any shift downward in their batting order could necessitate a re-evaluation of our daily caps.",
